reviews.review: Continuity is nonexistent, the plot was all over the place. There was some potential story arcs but went nowhere. Overall... horrible movie.
As good an ending as it could be given it had to recover from that horrendous Last Jedi film.
I loved it. From beginning to end! Great action and special effects. The story was great and tied up most of if not all the story lines.

I've read alot of reviews on this film, but not until after I actually watched it. Most that i read are bad saying the film is too nostalgic and not looking forward enough. Errrr, it's the last one. As far forward as you can look is the end credits. Theres no more. 
I'm a ESB fan. Best movie of the franchise imo. The prequels started bad but but episode 3 Ienjoyed them. Disney has taken over and has taken on a huge task of trying to make a fresh look at star wars and keep die hard fans happy. I love the new films. Last jedi had problems but still liked it. The finally is exactly that. A finally. And a dam good ride if you ask me. It's not without problems. Carrie Fisher scenes feel awkward, but a much needed farewell.  There is loads of nostalgia in this film. I mean but the bucket load. It's got a few twists and turns, and story is a typical star wars story, but what's bad about that? 
JJ Abrams was never going to please everyone, but in my opinion he knocked it out of the park and will miss old and new cast alike.  Bring on episode 10!!!!! Oh wait......
Quick note. My wife hates star wars.  This film didn't change her mind
Same story line! Same outcome! No wow factor. Id rather watch the original Star Wars movie many times over. What message did the director try to convey with this movie?
Donâ€™t listen to the so-called critics. Awesome movie and a great end to the Skywalker Saga.

Derivative crap that reheated plot points from Empire and ROTJ. If you think this movie was great, just re-watch the old ones and then let the the next filmmakers tell new stories while you wallow in nostalgia.

There was so much that had to be fixed from Last Jedi and I feel J.J did the best he could. The film is the most fast paced of the entire franchise, but how they handled it I felt was great. 7 was a carbon copy of 4. 8 completely went in a different direction of how Luke's arc was in the previous movies. But 9 was awesome. Of course certain parts I would've changed but overall a great movie and I wish J.J could've done all 3.
